rComments: He's the toughest professor in the PoliSci Department. That said, I learned a LOT. He's a bit quirky, so keep that in mind.
One of the best professors I have had at UTM. Very knowledgeable. Respectable. Interesting.

One of those professors who REALLY knows his stuff. Incredibly knowledgeable. Goes into a lot of detail, as you might expect from a third-year class, but really stands out from other UTM third-year classes in intensity. Lots of dense (but usually interesting) reading. Doing all of it isn't necessarily vital to doing well, but the context helps.

Professor Day is a great  lecturer, scholar and teacher. The breadth of his knowledge is evidenced by the rich content his courses, which seek to bring together political philosophy and political economy.
The best Prof I have ever had.

Prof. Day is one of UTM's most intelligent, researched, and reputable professors. POL309 is a challenging course; the lectures are much denser than anything I've ever taken before (which is why I loved it). Understanding dense lectures key to success. Do not take this course if you doubt your aptitude for political economy. Hardcore class. Awesome.
The most amazing class I have ever taken. He's such a talented and amazing professor, really wants the students to learn for themselves.

If you have very good notes (and hence attend class), this was probably one of the most interesting courses I have taken at uni. Amazing prof, very very knowledgeable! I would not recommend it to people who are bad note-takers though!
His an amazinf teacher!! I took many politics classes that he taught
